South Africa’s Gold Fields said it will buy a 50% stake in Asanko Gold Inc’s Ghana subsidiary and take a stake in the Canadian miner in a $202.6 million deal. Gold Fields said in a statement on Thursday that as well as acquiring half of Asanko Gold Ghana’s 90% interest in the Asanko Gold Mine, its Ghana subsidiary will also acquire associated properties and exploration rights in the African country. The deal includes an upfront payment of $165 million on closure of the transaction and a deferred payment of $20 million. Gold Fields’ subsidiary will also take a 9.9% stake in Toronto-listed Asanko for $17.6 million in a share placement.